rComments: This was my second time taking a class with Prof. Boucher as a French Immersion student and it's still just as easy to pass. Her exams are entirely open book and based on copying and pasting things from the readings. There is no textbook, it's all available through the library online. An easy A if you have a heavy semester.

rComments: Prof. Boucher is one of the sweetest professors I've ever had. She genuinely wants everyone in her classes to do well and does everything in her power to make sure you do. I took this 2nd yr french course as a 1st yr in french immersion and it was still very easy to understand her and her assignments. No textbook, just online articles to print.

rComments: Her way of presenting the course is through word . Make sure to write everything you see. midterm and exams and points for showing up. easy class, exams are open book!

such a nice woman.. her teaching style is different and her lecture notes might need to be improved cuz they're word docs style. once you get a hang of Her style and pace, she's not so bad.. attendance helps in order to get EXACT notes cuz exam is literally sifting thru open book notes to write EXACT answer. EASY A. participate for extra points
She's amazing, kind and caring, I highly recommend this professor! This course was really interesting and unique. One of the best geo prof I had

This class is an essay course, there is nothing to memorize, and to get an A in the class you need to do what she wants.  It's possible to do well but you need to put in a lot of work and research. She's willing to answer all your questions and she will tell you what to do to do well. Not recommended for non-geography students. Amazing prof!!
